@leolv123 
Are you sure that `GroupByMemoryMergedResult` changes the result? If `count` is just a column name, I suppose it will not be handled by `GroupByMemoryMergedResult`.

>but there are other problems, why there a 'count' field in the query results, data merging will execute GroupByMemoryMergedResult

It's a bug. test is a logic table with id as sharding key.
> select distinct id,name from test where id=1000
> will be converted to 
> select distinct id,name from test00 where id=1000

but the subquery can't routing to sharidng table:
> select count(1) from (select distinct id,name from test where id=1000)t;
> will be converted to 
> select count(1) from (select distinct id,name from test where id=1000)t;

